fields.title: One Rule to Rule Them All
Rules Changes
fields.rule:
-- You get 2 owners to present a rule change in the offseason (so we know there's legitimate interest), then for a rule to be implemented you need 7 owners to say yes.

-- For a rule to be implemented you need 7 owners to say yes. 

-- The rule doesn't get implemented until two seasons later. (I'm talking big changes like if I proposed we added tight end premium or some shit).

-- If there is a unanimous vote, the rule will be implemented in the upcoming season.

fields.title: Taxi Squads
fields.rule:
--  Only 1st and 2nd year players are allowed on the Taxi Squad.

-- Drafted rookies are automatically placed on the Taxi Squad immediately after they are drafted. No other players are allowed to be moved to the taxi squad.

-- If an owner promotes a player from the Taxi Squad to the active roster, he shall not be allowed to demote him again.

-- Players picked up via waivers may not be demoted to the Taxi Squad.

-- If a rookie on a taxi squad is acquired by trade, he shall be allowed to remain on the Taxi Squad of the new owner.

-- If a 2nd year player on a taxi squad is acquired by trade, he shall be automatically promoted to the active roster on the new club.

fields.title: Taxi Squad Raiding
fields.rule:
-- Any owner may claim a 2nd year player (rookies are protected) from another Taxi Squad under the following conditions:

-- You may only have one active claim at a time. You cannot claim another player until your last claim has been resolved.

-- The cost of a claim is a draft pick for the following season one round higher than the claimed players drafted round.

-- If the claimed player was a first round pick, the cost to claim is a first and second round pick for the following season.

-- The claiming owner must have the picks required to make the claim.

-- The precedence of pick claims is as follows: the owner’s original picks shall be used first. If the owner doesn't have his own pick in that round but has multiple picks from other owners in that round, the team getting raided gets to choose which of the picks will be used for compensation. If no picks from that round are available, then the next highest pick available shall be used instead.

--  If the claiming owner does not have the pick specified in the acquisition cost, he may specify during the claim that he is using a higher pick from the same draft - if substitution of the higher pick is not made public during the claim, the claim will be nullified.

-- The Taxi Squad owner shall have 48 hours to decide on one of three options: 1) Allow the claim to take place and receive the compensatory pick 2) Promote the player to their active roster 3) Trade away the player to another team

-- If the claimed player is acquired or traded to any team, he is IMMEDIATELY activated to the active roster and is no longer taxi squad eligible

-- If the owner with the rookie being claimed does not respond within the required time limit, the claim will be processed and the compensation pick(s) will be awarded

fields.title: Roster Construction
fields.rule:
-- 28 Players Per Team
-- 1 QB
-- 2 RB
-- 3 WR
-- 1 TE
-- 1 Flex (WR/RB/TE)
-- 1 Superflex (QB/WR/RB/TE)
-- 1 D/ST
-- 1 Nerfed Kicker
-- 3 IR Spots not counting towards roster total

fields.title: Trades
fields.rule:
-- Trades will go through automatically without a review period.
-- If someone thinks that there has been some sort of collusion, contact me, I'll assemble a committee of 3 owners who are not involved to make a decision on whether there was collusion or not.  If they determine there was collusion, the trade will be reversed.
-- Trading future draft picks is allowed and encouraged.
-- Currently, you may only trade picks up to two years in the future.
-- A trade deadline is enforced around week 12 of the season. Please view the ESPN league settings to verify.

fields.title: Free Agent Acquisition
fields.rule:
-- During the season we will have a Free Agent Blind Auction Budget. Budget of $100.
-- After the Championship, Free Agents will be locked.  You will be able to make trades throughout the offseason, but not add unrostered players to your team.  You can add those players to your team at the Rookie/Free Agent Draft!

fields.title: Scoring Settings
fields.rule:
-- Passing Yards:                     .04 pts/yd
-- Passing TD:                          4 pts
-- Interception:                         -2 pts
-- 2pt passing conversion:     2 pts
-- Rushing:                                0.1 pts/yd
-- Rushing TD:                          6 pts
-- 2 pt rush conversion:          2 pts
-- Receiving:                             0.1 pts/yd
-- Reception:                            0.5 ppr
-- Reception TD:                      6 pts
-- Return yards:                       0.05 pts/yd
-- Return TD:                           6 pts
-- Fumble:                               -1 pt
-- Fumble lost:                       -1 pt ( -2 points total for lost fumble)
